displayTitle: When every day's a grand adventure
title: Text Title

body: Sprout provides clothing for babies and toddlers who are exploring the big wide world for the very first time. To sprout is to grow, and Sprout's clothing range is designed for adventure, being playful and having fun like only kids know how. Come along for the ride in this Learning Moment about Sprout and learn everything you need to know about this Myer Exclusive Brand (MEB).
title: Text Title

title: Text Title

body:
Sprout clothing is designed under two banners: the essentials program and fashion program, both of which are clearly merchandised in-store. These combine to provide outfitting solutions for every imaginable occasion.

The essentials program is available in toddler, newborn (available summer 2019) and sleepwear ranges, and covers casual, day-to-day wear. It offers terrific low prices, especially when part of a 2-for deal. The coordinated, multi-outfit essentials offerings really set Sprout apart from other brands and make add-on selling a cinch.

Our fashion program ranges are released monthly for both teeny tiny newborns (sized 0000 to 0) and adventurous tots aged zero to two. These are designed for special events and gifting, and incorporate the latest market trends (like impossibly cute faux-fur jackets!).
title: Text Title

_items.body:
Fashion Program

All set to play in an adorable example of Sprout’s fashion program offerings.

Sleepwear

Ready to explore their dreams in super-cute Sprout sleepwear, which includes pj sets, dressing gowns and baby sleeping bags.

Swimwear

Waiting to make a splash in Sprout’s swimwear, released during the warmer months. Our new chlorine resistant range will be available from July 2018 in sizes 000 to 2.

body: Opportunities to explore the world are limitless when you’re a little tyke, and Sprout’s unique range – priced between $12.95 and $39.95 during the warmer seasons and increasing to $54.95 for winter coats in the colder months – has got you covered no matter what the occasion, whether you’re off to the beach, playing in the park or going nigh nighs. The following outfits are just a taste of what adventures await… see the current catalogue in your store to continue exploring.
title: Narrative Title

body:
Sprout is the perfect gifting destination because everyone – not just mum and dad – gets excited about the arrival of a new baby or celebrating a little angel's first birthday. Grandparents, aunties, uncles, cousins, friends and neighbours will all be on the lookout for the perfect gift and are as much Sprout’s customers as parents are.

This broad audience means team members have loads of opportunities to sell. It also means that some customers will need more guidance than others, particularly around things like sizing. Which leads us to the next section…
title: Text Title

body: One of the most important ways team members can help customers select the right garment is by understanding how Sprout’s sizing works:

body: All of Sprout’s brand labels have been updated to include the child’s age as well as the size, as in the following example, which is a plus for both team members and customers!
title: Text Title

_items.backText: Every piece of Sprout clothing is strictly tested and measured to ensure only the best fit and quality is achieved. Most of the range is 100% cotton, which makes for more breathable and durable clothing.

Sprout’s designers dream up fun, fashionable creations, like this dude's 'Dino Mite' flocked T-shirt. The designs incorporate special details – appliqué, glitter, pompoms etc – which set them apart from competitors.
Sprout represents excellent value for money, especially when considering its top-notch quality. And that’s before taking any special offers, like a 2-for deal, into account!

Sprout uses only the softest, gentlest fabrics, ensuring its cuts fit perfectly and are comfortable for little ones. Safety is a major factor in its production processes too – the team adheres to the strictest Australian standards.

body: Sprout is designed at Myer’s head office in Melbourne. Its range is available at every Myer store in Australia, making it easy to promote and to order sizes and colours not in your store via our myCustomer Orders (MCO) app (see the myCustomer Orders Learning Moment for more).
title: Text Title

_items.body: That’s such a gorgeous T-shirt and shorts combination you’ve selected! Are you aware that you can get two T-shirts for $20? Could I perhaps show you another tee that would also look adorable with the shorts you've already chosen?
_items.title: SPECIAL OFFERS

_items.body: Have you seen Sprout’s selection of beanies and tights? I could show you some that would look absolutely delightful with this dress you’re purchasing if you like?
_items.title: ADD-ON SELLING
SIZING
_items.body: So you’re after something for your sister’s four-month-old baby? Size 00 is what you’ll need to buy. Let me show you the labels on our garments to help you further understand how the sizing for babies works.

_items.title: SAFETY
_items.body: I hear your concern about safety with children’s clothing and can reassure you that Sprout garments follow the strictest safety compliance standards for childrenswear.

Here’s where this Sprout journey ends, but for you it’s just the beginning: you now have the chance to delight customers with your Sprout knowledge and help them find exactly what they’re after when shopping for this MEB.


Be sure to also check out the Milkshake Learning Moment – a MEB for girls and boys aged three to eight – so you’ll be able to assist parents with different aged kids in tow.


Myer’s other childrenswear MEBs include Jack & Milly (for newborns to six-year-old girls and boys), Tilii (girls eight to 16) and Bauhaus (boys eight to 16). See their ranges – along with Milkshake's and more Sprout fashion – at the following links.
